\name{qvivid-package}
\alias{qvivid}
\alias{qvivid-package}
\docType{package}
\title{Fast Quantum Simulation and Vivid Visualizations}
\description{
Builds, simulates, inspects, and animates gate-based quantum circuits with an
R-native API, a compiled statevector backend, reproducible sampling,
phase-aware graphics, reduced-state Bloch spheres, and journal-sized exports.
}
\details{
The package uses one-based qubit indices. Qubit 1 is the least significant
statevector bit, while displayed basis labels use conventional high-to-low
order. Use \code{\link{quantum_circuit}} to begin.
}
